         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="2.14d-2.18c"/>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>sta</w><w>ekalymi</w><pc>•</pc><num value="14">10-4</num>
<w>gṛ<lb corresp="#a2"/><supplied>ddhā</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>te</w><w>ratā</w><pc>•</pc><w>s<supplied>n</supplied>ai</w>
<lb corresp="#b1"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>di</supplied>vy<supplied>e</supplied>ṣu</w><w><supplied>kā</supplied>me<choice><orig>p</orig><corr>ṣ</corr></choice>u</w><pc>•</pc>
<lb corresp="#b2"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>yänmāṣṣäṃ</w><pc>•</pc>
<w>tṛṣṇākṣaya<lb/><supplied>rataḥ</supplied></w></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (desire does not) control (him). [SKT] (men who are) eager (for desires and negligent)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] they are pleased (with the unlawful indeed) [TB] (they are pleased with the) un(lawful indeed)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (even) for divine desires</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] (he) obtains (no delight) [SKT] he delights in the destruction of craving</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>116-117</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:chakravarti1930"/><citedRange>26-29</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>19</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>29</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="remarks">Probably the upper margin of the recto (lower of the verso) and the right margin are preserved.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.2.14d-15a <hi>tṛṣṇā na kurute vaśam // 14 gṛddhā hi kāmeṣu narāḥ pramattā</hi></note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.2.15b <hi>hy adharme bata te ratāḥ</hi></note><note corresp="#b1" type="philcomment">Uv.2.18a <hi>api divyeṣu kāmeṣu</hi>, see Dhp. 187</note><note corresp="#b2" type="philcomment">Uv.2.18b-c <hi>sa ratiṃ nādhigacchati | tṛṣṇākṣayarato bhavati</hi>, see Dhp. 187</note></p>
         </div>
